        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">put the "%t is snared" "%t is feared" onto the same hotkey as the darkness/fear spell but make it say something like "attempting to fear %t"....</P><P>if Darkness is in spell slot 1...<BR>/cast 1<BR>/g Attempting to Snare %t<BR>i'm not sure if you need a /pause or not...if so just throw a /pause 10 (which is 1 second) onto it.</P><P>/cast 1<BR>/pause 10<BR>/g Attempting to snare %t!</P><P>also personally the only pet commands i keep on my main page is /pet attack and /pet back off.  i've gotten rather used to shift+# to jump around banks...even after they added the extra 4 slots i still would do shift+2, 2 to FD...i had FD on my main page but since i always did the other way i just put something else there.</P><P>right now on my main page i have...<BR>1) spell (normally lich or self buff)<BR>2) splurt (or main/first DoT i'm using)<BR>3) BoD<BR>4) pet attack<BR>5) darkness (or a second DoT or drain if on a raid)<BR>6) fear/root/st (or again if on a raid it is normally another DoT or heal)<BR>7)CoS<BR>8)---(this is where my FD used to be, forget what i have now...*shrug* it is early)<BR>9) spell (this slot here basically is just whatever other random spell i feel like having up)<BR>10) pet back off<BR>---<BR>Page 2<BR>1) HS<BR>2) FD<BR>------<BR>basically the rest of my hotkeys are just scattered in an odd way that works for me...can't recall what it is off the top of my head but i know what they are as i hit them, hehe.</P><P><marquee>ABILLISTER "MONKEY" ABU-Povar</marquee><BR><marquee><a href="<a href="http://www.theinverselogic.com" target="_blank">http://www.theinverselogic.com</a>">Inverse Logic</a></marquee><BR><marquee>I had a Monkey named Steve, who picked Berries from Trees. Have you seen my Monkey named Steve?</marquee><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
