        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I do not set hotkeys for casting spells...I use the alt + "spell gem number" to cast my spells.  See no need to waste hotkeys for it.  Once you get used to it, you will never go back!  LOL!</P><P>I have my jboots, loc, sense heading, assist, pet guard here, pet attack, pet back off, pet sit, and pet follow as my primary hot keys.</P><P>I find groups don't care much to hear when I cast all my spells.  If I am with a pickup group I let them know what I am doing, though.  Sometimes I let people know what I am doing to humor the situation.  I like to come up with wierd things to say like...</P><P>"And your first born shall DIE!!!!  A %T has been PLAGUED!!!"  <BR>or <BR>"Bonding with %T in the Shadows!!" <BR>or <BR>"%T has been Ishtarrarized!  Kill it while it runs!"  </P><P>I used to say "%T has been DOOOOOOMED!! Kill it while it's SLOW!"  But peeps thought I was slowing things like a chanter or shammy.  So, I had to change it to "%T has been snared with darkness!" to keep the confusion down.</P><P>I also play in full screen mode with 1024X768.  Very nice.  I use ctrl+S for sitting and crt+B for spellbook and ctrl+X for camping.  I remapped ctrl+D so that is no longer drops me from my group...my fat fingers got annoying that way  LOL!</P><P>Edited by - ishtarra on 10/31/2001  08:06:24</P><P>Edited by - ishtarra on 11/01/2001  08:33:08<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
