        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=69554&TOPIC_ID=7855&FORUM_ID=11&CAT_ID=5&Forum_Title=Newbie+Hall&Topic_Title=Hot+Buttons%3A+What%27s+Your+Layout%3F&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Something I've found now that I'm playing a caster is that I was running out of buttons and didn't like swaping between the banks. </P><P>I started looking around and found that you could map the spells to letters, so now I have mapped all my spells to the letter below the number. q,w,e,r,t,y,u,i</P><P>Now I have quick access to them while not taking a place on the bank and I can look at the number just above the letter if I need to know what number I want to hit.</P><P>Also, for meding, I have mapped that to a letter also.  Once again, getting rid of a button.  By doing that it opens my book to the last page I was on.</P><P>I use one of the buttons for a con/sense heading so I get my SH skill up, and a button (when in groups) for /assist pullername, /pause 10, con  so I see what my puller has got us into.  Oh, and my %t mob is mezzed don't touch it button.</P><P>I'm almost sure you can map pet commands to keys also, but I have yet to look at them.  Just by doing the above, I have lots of room in my buttons for the situation (group, no group, travel). I will have LOTS of room if I can get my few pet commands out also (Solo, I have sit, stand/guard here, Attack, get back here) (grouped it have attack, and get back here as he usually doesn't take much damage to have to sit)</P><P>Oh, slot 10 is always FD so I have two buttons I can hit when getting molested. 10 and "I".</P><P>Good luck out there.</P><P>-Darkvane</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
